"use strict";(self.webpackChunk=self.webpackChunk||[]).push([[7514],{5738:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"BLACK_AFRICANS_CAPTIVITY","metadata":{"permalink":"/web/poems/BLACK_AFRICANS_CAPTIVITY","source":"@site/poems/Kumo1.md","title":"BLACK AFRICANS CAPTIVITY","description":"","date":"2023-03-08T18:17:22.000Z","formattedDate":"March 8, 2023","tags":[{"label":"Writing","permalink":"/web/poems/tags/writing"},{"label":"poems","permalink":"/web/poems/tags/poems"}],"readingTime":0.02,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Auwal Ismail Kumo","title":"Student @ GSU","url":"https://www.facebook.com/auwal.ismailkumo","imageURL":"https://scontent.fabv3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/323024127_401910922128299_1551404386257245821_n.jpg?_nc_cat=103&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=09cbfe&_nc_ohc=0bhcJse4cLsAX8X930O&_nc_zt=23&_nc_ht=scontent.fabv3-1.fna&oh=00_AfBSC1gIACointU8LF4-JH010i-hz1LwGxYZJphM0y8Gvg&oe=63D509E5","key":"AuwalKumo"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"BLACK_AFRICANS_CAPTIVITY","title":"BLACK AFRICANS CAPTIVITY","authors":["AuwalKumo"],"tags":["Writing","poems"]},"nextItem":{"title":"Cashless Generation","permalink":"/web/poems/Cashless_Generation"}},"content":"\x3c!-- ![](img/ccgsu.jpg) --\x3e\\n\\n![](kumo/20-11-2022.jpg)"},{"id":"Cashless_Generation","metadata":{"permalink":"/web/poems/Cashless_Generation","source":"@site/poems/clashe.md","title":"Cashless Generation","description":"","date":"2023-03-08T18:17:22.000Z","formattedDate":"March 8, 2023","tags":[{"label":"Writing","permalink":"/web/poems/tags/writing"},{"label":"Poems","permalink":"/web/poems/tags/poems"}],"readingTime":0.005,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"Cashless_Generation","title":"Cashless Generation","tags":["Writing","Poems"]},"prevItem":{"title":"BLACK AFRICANS CAPTIVITY","permalink":"/web/poems/BLACK_AFRICANS_CAPTIVITY"},"nextItem":{"title":"index","permalink":"/web/poems/index"}},"content":"![](img/cashless.png)"},{"id":"/index","metadata":{"permalink":"/web/poems/index","source":"@site/poems/index.md","title":"index","description":"","date":"2023-03-08T18:17:22.000Z","formattedDate":"March 8, 2023","tags":[],"readingTime":0,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"prevItem":{"title":"Cashless Generation","permalink":"/web/poems/Cashless_Generation"},"nextItem":{"title":"Interrogating your wandering spirit","permalink":"/web/poems/intergo"}},"content":""},{"id":"/intergo","metadata":{"permalink":"/web/poems/intergo","source":"@site/poems/intergo.md","title":"Interrogating your wandering spirit","description":"What do you see when you sleep?","date":"2023-03-08T18:17:22.000Z","formattedDate":"March 8, 2023","tags":[],"readingTime":0.825,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"prevItem":{"title":"index","permalink":"/web/poems/index"},"nextItem":{"title":"And This Is How We Rise Again","permalink":"/web/poems/We_Rise_Again"}},"content":"What do you see when you sleep? \\nIs it a dream or a vision?\\nDoes he bear fangs and talons\\nScratching and biting you in sacred places\\nSavouring the sweetness of virgin blood?\\nDoes he carry clay in his palms\\nFixing you in all the places you broke\\nSoothing your fears with mystical melodies\\nLulling you back to your skin?\\nWhen you return\\nDo you arrive panting out of breath\\nFrantically searching for shadows in the dark\\nHolding your heart in your fingers\\nWondering if this is the last time\\nYou might get to feel their warmth?\\nDoes he leave you eyes glazed, lips trembling\\nShivering from the ecstasy of another life\\nFinding it\'s purpose through your womb\\nBasking in the beauty of its new home?\\nThis lethargy that you carry around\\nResembles the aura of a human matrix\\nNurturing the bones of a demigod\\nShould I tell you the story of Danae\\nOr we just agree that Mars too is a myth?\\n\\n\\n\\n\xa9JL Maikaho"},{"id":"We_Rise_Again","metadata":{"permalink":"/web/poems/We_Rise_Again","source":"@site/poems/jenet.md","title":"And This Is How We Rise Again","description":"Daily,","date":"2023-03-08T18:17:22.000Z","formattedDate":"March 8, 2023","tags":[{"label":"Writing","permalink":"/web/poems/tags/writing"},{"label":"Poems","permalink":"/web/poems/tags/poems"}],"readingTime":2.325,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"We_Rise_Again","title":"And This Is How We Rise Again","tags":["Writing","Poems"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Interrogating your wandering spirit","permalink":"/web/poems/intergo"},"nextItem":{"title":"A Son, A Bandit, and A Victim","permalink":"/web/poems/jwang"}},"content":"Daily,\\nMonsters prowl our streets,  \\nHeaven on their lips, hell in their souls\\nInciting terror in our hearts yet, \\nWearing the cassocks of peace.\\nAbductions and molestation lining their path\\nIntertwined with guns, hate speeches and blood\\nCareless posts on social media\\nPushing us from pan to fire,\\nDeafening cries of men and women \\nScreaming for help.\\n\\nInstead,\\nOur eyes dwell on the North and South fighting\\nAnd the once tranquil west now joining in the\\nPandemonium, wreaking havoc\\nIn a country where nobody is safe.\\nUnable to tell our stories\\nYet able to shine the spotlight on those \\nErroneously labelled \'outsiders\'\\n\\n\'They don\'t like us either\'\\n\'They killed my brother in their village \\nSo I will kill their kinsman in my state!\'\\n\'They started it!\'\\n\'They deserved it!\'\\n\\nAnd so the blood feud continues,\\nFuelled by deceit shrouded in truth.\\nThe fiery shackles of fake news and half-truths\\nHolding our people captives,\\nCirculating filthy lies signed in God\'s holy name,\\nInciting more violence while pretending to solve the problem.\\n\\nDo you not know,\\nNo nation can rise by burying its weak and poor,\\nNo country can grow by ignoring the plight of its people  \\nLabelled minorities and refugees in their own country.\\nIndeed,\\nA cancer in one cell will engulf the whole system if left unchecked. \\n\\nWho can challenge the cycle of woes strangling our country?\\nWho dares to open her lips and sing of serenity?\\nWho is he that\'ll take the courage to break these chains,\\nAnd lead Nigeria to a new life of justice, integrity and transparency;\\nWhere every citizen gets a taste of what independence truly means? \\n\\nTune in to this channel and let me tell you a story:\\nA new tide is rising, powerful and determined\\nTongues sharpened by pain and language,\\nDrunk with the elixir in which creativity and activism meet.\\n\\nThis is the voice of the new Nigeria,\\nRising from within the bellows of its creatives.\\nEvery note and melody, every line and stanza,\\nEvery splash of colour from the painter\'s brush, \\nEvery script, every headline, every stroke of the sculptor\'s knife;\\nJoining their voices to challenge the single stories\\nThat have marred the beauty in our diversity.\\nGiving a voice to the humanity \\nStubbornly fighting inspite of the odds.\\n\\nLike a stone thrown into a pond,\\nRipples of patriotism are echoed from Chibok to Owo, \\nDapchi to Nnewi and Daura and Warri;\\nYoung and old ignited by fresh perspectives,\\nRefusing to remain silent,\\nBreaking free with chants of liberty, liberty for all!\\nRe-learning national identity, \\nQuestioning every rumour,\\nAnalysing every evidence,\\nInvestigating every tale,\\nCrushing the rock of propaganda \\nWith the hammer of right information\\nStreaming from our creatives -\\nInnovative, brilliant stars, \\nLeading us all to a nation we can truly be proud of. \\n\\nThank you."},{"id":"/jwang","metadata":{"permalink":"/web/poems/jwang","source":"@site/poems/jwang.md","title":"A Son, A Bandit, and A Victim","description":"Born at sunset,","date":"2023-03-08T18:17:22.000Z","formattedDate":"March 8, 2023","tags":[],"readingTime":0.6,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"prevItem":{"title":"And This Is How We Rise Again","permalink":"/web/poems/We_Rise_Again"},"nextItem":{"title":"MUSANYAR KUDI","permalink":"/web/poems/Musanyar kudi"}},"content":"Born at sunset, \\nI am a child weaned from fallen breast before time. \\nSon of a fertile ground \\nBut fed with thorns and thistles. \\n\\nI can only watch the spoilers \u2013 \\nThey glut and yawn and leak their oily fingers. \\nA seed, but I am taken to the mill; \\nFlour for bread, a means to an end. \\n\\nI am the child with the guns, \\nA pawn on this chessboard of terror. \\nA thorn in the flesh of many: \\nI am horror \u2013 a harvest of many errors. \\n\\nThe spoilers ate sour grapes \\nAnd my teeth is at edge. \\nBrought to sunset before dawn, \\nI am a child, a bandit, and a victim. \\n\\n\\nJ. D. Jwang \\n(The Child that Found Mercy)"},{"id":"Musanyar kudi","metadata":{"permalink":"/web/poems/Musanyar kudi","source":"@site/poems/kudi.md","title":"MUSANYAR KUDI","description":"","date":"2023-03-08T18:17:22.000Z","formattedDate":"March 8, 2023","tags":[{"label":"Writing","permalink":"/web/poems/tags/writing"},{"label":"Poems","permalink":"/web/poems/tags/poems"}],"readingTime":0.005,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Auwal Ismail Kumo","title":"Student @ GSU","url":"https://www.facebook.com/auwal.ismailkumo","imageURL":"https://scontent.fabv3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/323024127_401910922128299_1551404386257245821_n.jpg?_nc_cat=103&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=09cbfe&_nc_ohc=0bhcJse4cLsAX8X930O&_nc_zt=23&_nc_ht=scontent.fabv3-1.fna&oh=00_AfBSC1gIACointU8LF4-JH010i-hz1LwGxYZJphM0y8Gvg&oe=63D509E5","key":"AuwalKumo"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"Musanyar kudi","title":"MUSANYAR KUDI","authors":["AuwalKumo"],"tags":["Writing","Poems"]},"prevItem":{"title":"A Son, A Bandit, and A Victim","permalink":"/web/poems/jwang"},"nextItem":{"title":"MY NIRVANA","permalink":"/web/poems/my_nirvana"}},"content":"![](img/kudi.png)"},{"id":"my_nirvana","metadata":{"permalink":"/web/poems/my_nirvana","source":"@site/poems/kumo.md","title":"MY NIRVANA","description":"","date":"2023-03-08T18:17:22.000Z","formattedDate":"March 8, 2023","tags":[{"label":"Writing","permalink":"/web/poems/tags/writing"},{"label":"Poems","permalink":"/web/poems/tags/poems"}],"readingTime":0.01,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Auwal Ismail Kumo","title":"Student @ GSU","url":"https://www.facebook.com/auwal.ismailkumo","imageURL":"https://scontent.fabv3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/323024127_401910922128299_1551404386257245821_n.jpg?_nc_cat=103&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=09cbfe&_nc_ohc=0bhcJse4cLsAX8X930O&_nc_zt=23&_nc_ht=scontent.fabv3-1.fna&oh=00_AfBSC1gIACointU8LF4-JH010i-hz1LwGxYZJphM0y8Gvg&oe=63D509E5","key":"AuwalKumo"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"my_nirvana","title":"MY NIRVANA","authors":["AuwalKumo"],"tags":["Writing","Poems"]},"prevItem":{"title":"MUSANYAR KUDI","permalink":"/web/poems/Musanyar kudi"},"nextItem":{"title":"QUOTES","permalink":"/web/poems/Quotes"}},"content":"![](img/ccgsu.jpg)\\n\\n![](kumo/22-11-2022.jpg)"},{"id":"Quotes","metadata":{"permalink":"/web/poems/Quotes","source":"@site/poems/qoutes.md","title":"QUOTES","description":"","date":"2023-03-08T18:17:22.000Z","formattedDate":"March 8, 2023","tags":[{"label":"Quotes","permalink":"/web/poems/tags/quotes"}],"readingTime":0.1,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"Quotes","title":"QUOTES","tags":["Quotes"]},"prevItem":{"title":"MY NIRVANA","permalink":"/web/poems/my_nirvana"},"nextItem":{"title":"The role of creative voices","permalink":"/web/poems/role"}},"content":"\x3c!-- ![](img/ccgsu.jpg) --\x3e\\n![](Qoutes/Abdulllahi.jpg)\\n![](Qoutes/Akko.jpg)\\n![](Qoutes/amaraci.jpg)\\n![](Qoutes/Divik.jpg)\\n![](Qoutes/Eveso.jpg)\\n![](Qoutes/Ezikel.jpg)\\n![](Qoutes/galadimah.jpg)\\n![](Qoutes/Geek.jpg)\\n![](Qoutes/Gimbiya.jpg)\\n![](Qoutes/halimah.jpg)\\n![](Qoutes/iseac.jpg)\\n![](Qoutes/kumu.jpg)\\n![](Qoutes/mailittafi.jpg)\\n![](Qoutes/magaji.jpg)\\n![](Qoutes/said.jpg)\\n![](Qoutes/smb.jpg)\\n![](Qoutes/yusuf.jpg)"},{"id":"/role","metadata":{"permalink":"/web/poems/role","source":"@site/poems/role.md","title":"The role of creative voices","description":"I see them building on acres,","date":"2023-03-08T18:17:22.000Z","formattedDate":"March 8, 2023","tags":[],"readingTime":0.745,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"prevItem":{"title":"QUOTES","permalink":"/web/poems/Quotes"},"nextItem":{"title":"SALUTE","permalink":"/web/poems/Salute"}},"content":"I see them building on acres,\\nwe haven\'t got the power,\\nbut our hands got the blessings,\\nwhich are important in the countries.\\n\\nBut listen to  my words which are infinite,\\nwhen it comes to a circle,\\nto write on the advantage,\\nnot only advantage,\\nbut also diversity,\\nin terms of helping society,\\nIn the presence, past, and future.\\n\\nIt\'s about the gallants,\\nthat have powers,\\nto change the mind of society,\\nin terms of  language grammar,\\nsince the year of a junior,\\nsection of students,\\nand this help to understand the language,\\nwhich is the lead of all subjects,\\none of the subjects include physics,\\nwhich help the engineers to \\nunderstand their category,\\nand even build a sky crapers,\\nthat society organisms,\\nlive on it without knowing,\\nit\'s the power of voices that\\n dedicated their pen ink,\\nwhich became crucial to the society.\\n\\n\u270d\ud83c\udfff\u270d\ud83c\udfff\u270d\ud83c\udfff\\nBin-bello\\nAbubakar Bello Gurama"},{"id":"Salute","metadata":{"permalink":"/web/poems/Salute","source":"@site/poems/salute.md","title":"SALUTE","description":"","date":"2023-03-08T18:17:22.000Z","formattedDate":"March 8, 2023","tags":[{"label":"Writing","permalink":"/web/poems/tags/writing"},{"label":"Poems","permalink":"/web/poems/tags/poems"}],"readingTime":0.02,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"Salute","title":"SALUTE","tags":["Writing","Poems"]},"prevItem":{"title":"The role of creative voices","permalink":"/web/poems/role"},"nextItem":{"title":"CC GSU president serah","permalink":"/web/poems/sheis"}},"content":"\x3c!-- ![](img/ccgsu.jpg) --\x3e\\n\\n![](img/salute.png)"},{"id":"/sheis","metadata":{"permalink":"/web/poems/sheis","source":"@site/poems/sheis.md","title":"CC GSU president serah","description":"","date":"2023-03-08T18:17:22.000Z","formattedDate":"March 8, 2023","tags":[],"readingTime":0.01,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"prevItem":{"title":"SALUTE","permalink":"/web/poems/Salute"},"nextItem":{"title":"Today is the day","permalink":"/web/poems/today"}},"content":"![](img/sera.png)\\n\\n![](img/sheis.png)"},{"id":"/today","metadata":{"permalink":"/web/poems/today","source":"@site/poems/today.md","title":"Today is the day","description":"","date":"2023-03-08T18:17:22.000Z","formattedDate":"March 8, 2023","tags":[],"readingTime":0.005,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"prevItem":{"title":"CC GSU president serah","permalink":"/web/poems/sheis"},"nextItem":{"title":"THE NEW NIGERIA: Role of creative voices","permalink":"/web/poems/voice"}},"content":"![](img/today.png)"},{"id":"/voice","metadata":{"permalink":"/web/poems/voice","source":"@site/poems/voice.md","title":"THE NEW NIGERIA: Role of creative voices","description":"BY","date":"2023-03-08T18:17:22.000Z","formattedDate":"March 8, 2023","tags":[],"readingTime":1.81,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"prevItem":{"title":"Today is the day","permalink":"/web/poems/today"}},"content":"BY\\nRilwanu muhammed\\n\\nThe New Nigeria is a concept that has been embraced by many Nigerians in recent years. It is a concept that embraces new ideas, new opportunities, and new ways of doing things. As a nation, Nigeria is undergoing a transformation, and creative voices play a vital role in helping to shape this transformation.\\n\\nCreative voices are essential in helping to shape the identity of the New Nigeria. Through the use of art, music, literature, and other forms of expression, creative voices can help to define the values and ideals of the New Nigeria. Creative voices can be used to bring attention to issues that are important to Nigerians, to provide a platform for dialogues on important topics, and to celebrate the diversity of the country.\\n\\nCreative voices can also be used to foster innovation and entrepreneurship. By providing a platform for creative expression, entrepreneurs and innovators can develop new ideas and solutions that can help to improve the lives of Nigerians.\\n\\nCreative voices can also help to inspire a sense of pride in the country and its people, and can be used to promote the country\u2019s unique culture and way of life.\\n\\nCreative voices are also essential in helping to bridge the divides between different ethnic and religious groups in the country. Through the use of art, music, and literature, creative voices can help to create a sense of unity and understanding between different groups. This can help to foster an environment of peace and harmony, and can lead to a more prosperous future for all Nigerians.\\n\\nIn conclusion, creative voices are essential in helping to shape the identity of the New Nigeria. By providing a platform for expression, creativity, and innovation, creative voices can help to foster a sense of unity and understanding between different groups, and can help to promote the country\u2019s unique culture and way of life. \\n\\nCreative voices can also be used to bring attention to issues that are important to Nigerians, to provide a platform for dialogues on important topics, and to celebrate the diversity of the country. Through creative voices, the New Nigeria can be a place of opportunity, hope, and progress.\\n\xa9Ridwanullah"}]}')}}]);